  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math alttext=\"seven twenty fourths\"><mfrac>\n<mn>7</mn>\n<mn>24</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math>. An expression of the form <math alttext=\"RootIndex n StartRoot a Superscript m Baseline EndRoot\"><mroot><msup><mi>a</mi><mi>m</mi></msup><mi>n</mi></mroot></math>, where <math alttext=\"m\"><mi>m</mi>\n</math> and <math alttext=\"n\"><mi>n</mi>\n</math> are integers greater than <math alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn>\n</math> and <math alttext=\"a greater than or equals 0\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&ge;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, is equivalent to <math alttext=\"a Superscript StartFraction m Over n EndFraction\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mi>n</mi></mfrac></msup></math>. Therefore, the expression on the right-hand side of the given equation, <math alttext=\"RootIndex 3 StartRoot 4 Superscript 7 Baseline EndRoot\"><mroot><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>7</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mroot></math>, is equivalent to <math alttext=\"4 Superscript seven thirds\"><msup><mn>4</mn><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></math>. Thus, <math alttext=\"4 Superscript 8 c Baseline equals 4 Superscript seven thirds\"><msup><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></math>. It follows that <math alttext=\"8 c equals seven thirds\"><mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>8</mn>\n<mi>c</mi>\n</mrow>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>7</mn>\n<mn>3</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Dividing both sides of this equation by <math alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn>\n</math> yields <math alttext=\"c equals seven twenty fourths\"><mrow>\n<mi>c</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>7</mn>\n<mn>24</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Note that 7/24, .2916, .2917, 0.219, and 0.292 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer.</p>",
